# Etch-a-Sketch Grid

Hey there! This is a fun little Etch-a-Sketch web app where you can create your own grid and â€œdrawâ€ by just moving your mouse over the squares. Itâ€™s simple, interactive, and lets you pick how big your grid is!



## What It Does

- Lets you choose a grid size from 1 to 100 (so, for example, a 16 means a 16Ã—16 grid)
- When you hover over any square, it changes color to black â€” just like drawing!
- The squares automatically adjust so the whole grid fits nicely inside a 600Ã—600 pixel box
- Every time you change the grid size, it wipes the old grid clean and starts fresh


## How To Use It

1. Open the `index.html` file in your favorite browser.
2. Click the **Change Grid** button.
3. Enter a number between 1 and 100 when prompted. This will be the width and height of your grid.
4. Move your mouse over the squares to start coloring and â€œdrawing.â€
5. Want a different grid? Just click **Change Grid** again and enter a new number!



